.START 

Minnesota State Rep. Phyllis Kahn believes society often ignores the needs of children because they lack real political power.
So she has introduced a bill to grant the vote in Minnesota to anyone 12 years of age or older.
When her idea was met with peals of laughter Rep. Kahn said her critics displayed an "adult supremacy attitude." It's more likely they fear a new political bidding war in which pork barrel projects are passed to attract votes from this new constituency.
Nintendo stamps, anyone? 

